The paper deals with distributed algorithms for computing approximate distances and routes in graphs, which is a problem in distributed computing (cs.DC) and graph algorithms (cs.DS). The use of small messages and the focus on communication complexity suggests a possible categorization in networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) or social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the use of approximation algorithms and the analysis of their performance suggests a possible categorization in algorithms (cs.AL).
